code:
```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='source', y='target', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between source and target?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='source', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['source'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['source'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['source'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['source'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of source?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Source')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
